{{Infobox football match | title = 2001 Supercopa de España | image = | event = | team1 = [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]] | team1association = | team1score = 1 | team2 = [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] | team2association = | team2score = 4 | details = on aggregate | firstleg = First leg | team1score1 = 1 | team2score1 = 1 | details1 = | date1 = 19 August 2001 | stadium1 = [[La Romareda]] | city1 = [[Zaragoza]] | man_of_the_match1a = | man_of_the_match1atitle = | man_of_the_match1b = | man_of_the_match1btitle = | referee1 = [[Antonio Jesús López Nieto|Antonio López Nieto]] | attendance1 = 26,800 | weather1 = | secondleg = Second leg | team1score2 = 0 | team2score2 = 3 | details2 = | date2 = 22 August 2001 | stadium2 = [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium|Santiago Bernabéu]] | city2 = [[Madrid]] | man_of_the_match2a = | man_of_the_match2atitle = | man_of_the_match2b = | man_of_the_match2btitle = | referee2 = [[Eduardo Iturralde González]] | attendance2 = 70,000 | weather2 = | previous = [[2000 Supercopa de España|2000]] | next = [[2002 Supercopa de España|2002]] }}
The '''2001 Supercopa de España''' was two-leg [[Football in Spain|Spanish]] [[football (soccer)|football]] matches played on 19 August and 22 August 2001. It was contested by [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]], who were [[Copa del Rey]] winners in [[2000–01 Copa del Rey|2000–01]], and [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]], who won the [[2000–01 La Liga|2000–01]] [[La Liga]] title. Real Madrid won the Supercopa de España 4&ndash;1 on aggregate.
