The '''2006 Orange Prokom Open''' was the ninth edition of this men's [[tennis]] tournament and was played on [[clay court|outdoor clay courts]]. The tournament was part of the [[ATP International Series|International Series]] of the [[2006 ATP Tour]]. It took place in [[Sopot]], [[Poland]] from July 31 through August 6, 2006.

==Champions==

===Men's Singles===
{{main|2006 Orange Prokom Open – Singles}}
{{flagicon|RUS}} '''[[Nikolay Davydenko]]''' defeated {{flagicon|GER}} [[Florian Mayer]], 7–6<sup>(8–6)</sup>, 5–7, 6–4<ref>{{cite web|url= http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/tennis/5250406.stm|title=Davydenko battles to Sopot title |date=6 August 2006|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=18 December 2014}}</ref>
*It was Davydenko's 2nd title of the year and the 7th of his career.

===Men's Doubles===
{{main|2006 Orange Prokom Open – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|CZE}} '''[[František Čermák]]''' / {{flagicon|CZE}} '''[[Leoš Friedl]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Martín García (tennis)|Martín García]] / {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sebastián Prieto]], 6–3, 7–5
* It was Čermák's 3rd title of the year and the 13th of his career. It was Friedl's 3rd title of the year and the 14th of his career.

