{{Infobox handball club | clubname = Chekhovskie Medvedi | image = Chehovski Medvedi.png|frameless | full name = Chekhovskie Medvedi Handball Club | founded = 2001 | ground = [[Olimpiysky Sport Palace (Chekhov, Moscow Oblast)|Olimpiysky Sport Palace]] | capacity = 3,000 | chairman = | manager = [[Vladimir Maksimov]] | league = [[Russian Handball Super League]] | season = 2017–18 | position = [[Russian Handball Super League]], '''1st''' | colour1 = Purple|colour2=White | website = http://www.ch-medvedi.ru/ |pattern_la1=_blueshoulders|pattern_b1=_thinbluesides|pattern_ra1=_redshoulders |leftarm1=FFFFFF|body1=FFFFFF|rightarm1=FFFFFF|shorts1=FFFFFF|socks1=FFFFFF |pattern_la2=_whiteshoulders|pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2=_redshoulders |leftarm2=191970|body2=191970|rightarm2=191970|shorts2=191970|socks2=191970 }} '''Chekhovskie Medvedi''' ({{lang-ru|Чеховские Медведи}}, {{lang-en|Chekhov Bears}}) is a [[handball]] club from [[Chekhov, Moscow Oblast]], [[Russia]]. Chehovski Medvedi competes in the [[Russian Handball Super League]].
The organization was founded in 2001 on the basis of the disbanded [[HBC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow Handball Club]].
