=== Qualification paths ===
{{div col begin}}
*World Champion (1) *WWC: Women's World Champion 2018 (1) *WC: Semi-finalists of the [[Chess World Cup 2017]] (4) *J17 and J18: [[World Junior Chess Championship|World Junior Champions]] 2017 and 2018 (2) *R: Rating (average of all published ratings from February 2018 to January 2019 is used) (18) *E18 and E19: [[European Individual Chess Championship|European Individual Championships]] 2018 (23) and 2019 (22) *AM18 and AM19: [[Pan American Chess Championship|American Continental Championships]] 2018 (4) and 2019 (4) *AS18 and AS19: [[Asian Chess Championship]]s 2018 (5) and 2019 (5) *AF: [[African Chess Championship]] 2019 (2) *[[Nordic Chess Championship]] (N), [[U.S. Chess Championship|Z2.1]] (5),[[Canadian Chess Championship|Z2.2]] (1), Z2.3 (2), Z2.4 (2), Z2.5 (2), Z3.1 (1), Z3.2 (1), Z3.3 (2), Z3.4 (2), Z3.5 (2), [[Oceania Chess Championship|Z3.6]] (1), [[Indian Chess Championship|Z3.7]] (1), Z4.1 (1), Z4.2 (1), Z4.3 (1), Z4.4 (1): Zonal tournaments *ACP: highest-placed participant of the [[Association of Chess Professionals#ACP Tour and Tournaments|ACP Tour]] who has not qualified with the previous criteria (1) *PN: [[Kirsan Ilyumzhinov|FIDE President]] nominee (5) *ON: Organizer nominee (4)</small> {{div col end}} <!-- ==Results, rounds 1–4==
