{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Deer Park | nickname = | country = England | image = Dunstallcc.jpg | location = [[Dunstall]], [[Staffordshire]] | establishment = 1997 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year2 = 1999 | club2 = [[Derbyshire Cricket Board]] | year1 = 1998 | club1 = [[Staffordshire County Cricket Club|Staffordshire]] | date = 14 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/459.html Ground profile }}
'''Deer Park''' is a [[cricket]] ground within the grounds of Dunstall Hall, [[Dunstall]], [[Staffordshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1997, when the [[Derbyshire County Cricket Club|Derbyshire Second XI]] played the [[Durham County Cricket Club|Durham Second XI]] in the [[Second XI Championship|Second XI Trophy]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/459_set.html Second XI Trophy Matches played on Deer Park]</ref> The ground held 2 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] matches in 1999. The first saw the [[Derbyshire Cricket Board]] as the home team against [[Shropshire County Cricket Club|Shropshire]] and the second saw [[Staffordshire County Cricket Club|Staffordshire]] against the [[Nottinghamshire Cricket Board]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/459_mint.html MCCA Knockout Trophy Matches played on Deer Park]</ref> The ground has held a number of [[Second XI Championship]]<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/459_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on Deer Park]</ref> and Second XI Trophy matches for the Derbyshire Second XI.
The ground has held a single [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match which saw the Derbyshire Cricket Board play [[Wales Minor Counties Cricket Club|Wales Minor Counties]] in the [[1999 NatWest Trophy]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/459_a.html List-A Matches played on Deer Park]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, Deer Park is the home ground of [[Dunstall Cricket Club]] who play in the [[Derbyshire Premier Cricket League]].<ref>[http://dunstall.play-cricket.com/ Dunstall Cricket Club]</ref>
