{{Infobox stadium | name = Estadio El Cobre de El Salvador | image = Fotoestadio.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = Estadio El Cobre | location = [[El Salvador, Chile]] | coordinates = {{coord|26|15|7|S|69|37|43|W|display=inline,title|source:dewiki}} | opened = {{Start date|1980|06|01}} | surface = grass | architect = [[Mario Recordón]] | capacity = 12,000<ref>[http://www.estadioseguro.gob.cl/estadio/el-cobre.html]</ref> | dimensions = 105 x 75 m | tenants = [[Cobresal]] | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Estadio El Cobre''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[El Salvador, Chile]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Cobresal]]. The stadium holds 12,000 people, which is more than the population of the town it is in, and was built in 1980.<ref>[http://www.estadioseguro.gob.cl/estadio/el-cobre.html]</ref>
