{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Kadir Has Sport Hall | image = [[File:Kadir Has Kongre ve Spor Merkezi Kayseri.jpg|250px]] | location = [[Kayseri]], [[Turkey]] | broke_ground = | opened = 2008 | owner = [[Kayseri Kaski Spor Kulübü]] | architect = [http://www.ofismimarca.com/eng/ Ofiss Mimarca] | contractor = | tenants = | seating_capacity = [[Basketball]]: 7,200<ref name=fiba>[http://turkey2010.fiba.com/pages/eng/fe/10/fwcm/event-guide/cities/Kayseri/p/arena.html Turkey2010.FIBA.com - KAYSERI - Arena.]</ref> }}
'''Kadir Has Sport Hall''' ({{lang-tr|Kadir Has Spor Salonu}}) is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] that is located in [[Kayseri]], [[Turkey]]. Together with [[Kadir Has Stadium|Kayseri Kadir Has Stadium]], it is a part of the Kayseri Kadir Has Sports Complex, one of the newest sports complexes in Turkey. Completed in 2008, the capacity of the arena is 7,200 spectators.<ref name=fiba/>
==History== Upon the withdrawal of the Antalya Arena project, the venue was appointed to be one of the five basketball halls selected for the [[2010 FIBA World Championship]]. The arena had a crucial role in Turkey's organization of the 2010 FIBA World Championship.
==See also== *[[Kadir Has Stadium]]
