{{NBA Development League Awards}}
The '''NBA Development League Most Valuable Player (MVP)''' is an annual [[NBA Development League]] (D-League) award given since the league's [[2001–02 NBDL season|inaugural season]] to the best performing player of the regular season. The league's head coaches determine the award by voting and it is usually presented to the honoree during the D-League playoffs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dleague.nba.com/news/jarnell-stokes-2015-16-nba-dleague-mvp/|title=Jarnell Stokes Named 2015-16 NBA Development League MVP|work=NBA.com|date=April 14, 2016|accessdate=April 15, 2016}}</ref>

No player has been named the MVP more than once, and no international player has won the award. [[Ansu Sesay]] was the inaugural winner while playing for the [[Greenville Groove]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/dleague/nbdl/groove_sesay_mvp_020327.html|title=Groove's Sesay Named 2001-02 NBDL MVP|work=NBA.com|date=March 27, 2002|accessdate=April 15, 2016}}</ref> By [[basketball position|position]], [[guard (basketball)|guards]] have dominated the award with 11 winners, followed by [[forward (basketball)|forwards]] with six. Only one [[center (basketball)|center]] has won, [[Courtney Sims]] in 2008–09.

