{{Infobox football club | clubname = Pele FC | image = Pele Football Club.png | image_size = 200px | fullname = Pele Football Club | nickname = | founded = 1971 | ground = [[Georgetown, Guyana|Georgetown]], [[Guyana]] | capacity = | chrtitle = | chairman = | mgrtitle = | manager = | league = [[GFF Elite League]] | season = | position = | current = | website = }}
'''Pele FC''' is a [[Guyana|Guyanese]] [[association football|football]] club based in [[Georgetown, Guyana|Georgetown]], competing in the [[GFF Elite League]], the top tier of Guyanese football. The club was founded in 1971 and is named after [[Brazil]]ian football legend [[Pelé]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/guyanafound.html|title=Guyana&nbsp;– List of Foundation Dates|accessdate=12 September 2015|publisher=RSSSF}}</ref>
