{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox football club | clubname = Salus | image = [[File:Escudo Salus Football Club.png|120px]]| fullname = Salus Football Club | nickname = ''Azulgrana'' (Blue and Red) | founded = 10 April 1928 | ground = Parque Salus| capacity = 4.000| chairman = Gabriel Noil | manager = Juan Carlos Paz | league = [[Segunda División Amateur de Uruguay|Segunda División Amateur]]| season = | position = | |Web = http://www.salusfc.com/ |pattern_la1=_salus2014-15h |pattern_b1=_salus2014-15h |pattern_ra1=_salus2014-15h |pattern_sh1=_salus2014-15h |leftarm1=0000ff |body1=ff0000 |rightarm1=0000ff |shorts1=0000ff |socks1=0000ff |pattern_la2=_salus2014-15a |pattern_b2=_salus2014-15a |pattern_ra2=_salus2014-15a |pattern_sh2=_salus2014-15a |leftarm2=FFFFFF |body2=FFFFFF |rightarm2=FFFFFF |shorts2=FFFFFF |socks2=FFFFFF }}
'''Salus Football Club''' is a [[association football|football]] club from [[Montevideo, Uruguay]]. They currently play in the [[Segunda División Amateur de Uruguay|Second Amateur Division]],the third and last tier of the [[Campeonato Uruguayo de Fútbol|Uruguayan championship]].
