{{Infobox sport governing body |name = South African Taekwondo Federation |abbrev = SATF |logo = South African Taekwondo Federation Logo.jpeg |logosize = |sport = [[Taekwondo]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = [[South Africa]] |founded = |aff = [[World Taekwondo]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldtaekwondo.org/about-wt/members/mna/?member_id=4224|title=MNA - World Taekwondo|website=WT|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref> |affdate = 1991 |region = [[African Taekwondo Union]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftu.org/member.php?id=36|title=African Taekwondo Union : South Africa|website=AFTU|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref> |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Pretoria]] |location = 256 Danie Theron Street, [[Pretoria North]] 0016, [[Gauteng]] |president = Godfrey Mokoboto |chairman = |chairperson = |chair = |chiefexec = |vicepresident = |director = |secretary = Wiehann Koen |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = |countryflag = South Africa }}
'''South African Taekwondo Federation''' is the [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for the [[sport]] of [[taekwondo]] in [[South Africa]] and a member of the world governing body, [[World Taekwondo]] (WT) (formerly called [[World Taekwondo Federation]]) along with the continental governing body, [[African Taekwondo Union]] (AFTU). South African Taekwondo Federation is also registered with the [[South African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee]] (SASCOC).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://staging.sascoc.co.za/2014/01/21/taekwondo-federation-of-south-africa/|title=South African Taekwondo Federation|website=SASCOC|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref>
South African Taekwondo Federation organises national competitions including the Ambassadors Cup, which is a popular fixture on its calendar, organised in partneship with the Korean Embassy in South Africa, and held annually since 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreanetblog.blogspot.com/2016/05/taekwondo-outdoors-in-south-africa.html?m=1|title=Taekwondo outdoors in South Africa|website=Korea Blog|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.korea.net/NewsFocus/Sports/view?articleId=105461|title=Taekwondo grows dreams in Africa|website=Korea.net|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref>
{{portal|Martial arts}}
