{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Carl Lewis International Complex | nickname = | image = | fullname = Tom Tellez Track at the Carl Lewis International Complex | location = Houston, Texas | coordinates = | broke_ground = 1999 | built = | opened = 2000 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[University of Houston System]] | operator = [[University of Houston]] | surface = | construction_cost = $4 Million<ref name="New facility">{{cite web |url=http://www.thedailycougar.com/static/vol65/123/sports/sports2.html |title=UH's new facility to open this weekend |author=Carpenter, Tom |date=2000-03-31 |publisher=''The Daily Cougar'' |accessdate=2008-05-29}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Houston Cougars]] [[track & field]] ([[NCAA]]) (2000-Present) | seating_capacity = 6,000 | dimensions = | scoreboard = }} The '''Tom Tellez Track at Carl Lewis International Complex''', also known as simply '''Tom Tellez Track''' or '''Carl Lewis International Complex''', is home to the [[Houston Cougars]] outdoor track & field teams. The facility is named after [[Tom Tellez]] and [[Carl Lewis]], two of the most notable individuals to have been associated with the program.
The track features a European style design with wider curves and shorter straightaways than most U.S. tracks to enhance the speed of runners.<ref name="New facility" />
